headline: Labcorp (NYSE:LH) Misses Q4 CY2025 Sales Expectations
summary: Healthcare diagnostics company Labcorp Holdings (NYSE:LH) fell short of the market’s revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025, but sales rose 5.6% year on year to $3.52 billion. On the other hand, the company’s outlook for the full year was close to analysts’ estimates with revenue guided to $14.7 billion at the midpoint. Its non-GAAP profit of $4.07 per share was 3.2% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
